Try the sport of fencing. Fencing is an intensive physical replica of a computer game in which the mind must race quickly and the body must respond to meet the unforeseen challenges. Kidiosity was created to prioritize and protect the precious quality time that parents spend with their kids. In a world of seemingly endless demands on parents, too often the first thing that falls off our plate is the intentional, quality time we spend connecting with our kids. And that leads to stress and anxiety.

Not anymore. Kidiosity is here to deliver ideas, learning, and conversation starters to the mobile device of a mom or dad (or even a grandparent, nanny, or babysitter). Whatever time you have available, we’ll help you fill it with laughter, teachable moments, and lifelong memories.

data.description: We are a coding studio with a physical location in Austin, TX that opened in 2018.  We teach coding to kids ages 7+ and adults to solve problems with digital solutions!  We run virtual and in-person classes and camps.  We specialize in teaching problem-solving and critical thinking through coding.  Our teachers introduce students to hot topics like robotics, Python, Graphic Design, Web development, and more, using a variety of platforms to train the next generation of innovators.
